body:
While writing the [manual test list](https://gist.github.com/andymikulski/0a61c0742f87c1c3d26804481cc93620), I realized a lot of the functionality could/should have automated tests. So... now we have [40 more tests](https://gist.github.com/andymikulski/121193a38c445148a3faec62f18e4798)! I wrote a bunch of tests for the simple/non-`connect`ed components that build out the active filters, as well as some missing tests for the filter selectors.

@rehandalal / @mythmon , if y'all could review https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/405/commits/e3243c52e3fb3107112fe10aae72f9b24118d884 that would be awesome. Most of the tests are straight-forward.

@chartjes If you want to check out the manual instructions [here](https://gist.github.com/andymikulski/0a61c0742f87c1c3d26804481cc93620), you can find the handful of things I didn't write tests for.

